<L>__{interior keeper's lodge barton park day}
<A>__{sir john and brandon are cleaning their guns in companionable silence a habit left over from army days. sir john eyes brandon roguishly.}
<C>__{sir john}
<D>__{you know what they're saying, of course...}
<A>__{no answer.}
<C>__{sir john}
<D>__{the word is that you have developed a taste for certain company.}
<A>__{brandon stays resolutely silent. sir john is emboldened.}
<C>__{sir john}
<D>__{and why not, say i. a man like you in his prime she'd be a most fortunate young lady }
<A>__{brandon cuts across him.}
<C>__{colonel brandon}
<D>__{marianne dashwood would no more think of me than she would of you, john.}
<C>__{sir john}
<D>__{brandon, my boy, do not think of yourself so meanly }
<C>__{colonel brandon}
<D>__{and all the better for her.}
<A>__{sir john subsides. brandon is clearly as angry with himself as he is with sir john.}
